<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/820</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-10T19:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1107. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 54. Your 44, Embassy’s 1293, May 3, 9 p.m. We consider Spain’s
                                defaults have been condoned by us to such an extent as to <pb facs="0848" n="1682" xml:id="pg_1682"/> make starting afresh
                                impossible if by that expression you mean putting an end to the
                                agreement.</p>
                            <p>
                                <persName>Alfred G. Smith</persName>, shipping expert, sails for
                                Spain next week and will take up with you shipping end of
                                negotiations. Cable your home address.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>